      <dct:title xml:lang="en">skarn</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">skarn</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Metasomatic rock consisting mainly of Ca-, Mg-, Fe-, or Mn-silicate minerals, which are free from or poor in water. Typically formed at the contact between a silicate rock or magma and a carbonate rock.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Metasomatic rock consisting mainly of Ca-, Mg-, Fe-, or Mn-silicate minerals, which are free from or poor in water. Typically formed at the contact between a silicate rock or magma and a carbonate rock.</skos:definition>
