      <dct:title xml:lang="en">iron rich sedimentary material</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">iron rich sedimentary material</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Sedimentary material of unspecified consolidation state that consists of at least 50 percent iron-bearing minerals (hematite, magnetite, limonite-group, siderite, iron-sulfides), as determined by hand-lens or petrographic analysis. Corresponds to a rock typically containing 15 percent iron by weight.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Sedimentary material of unspecified consolidation state that consists of at least 50 percent iron-bearing minerals (hematite, magnetite, limonite-group, siderite, iron-sulfides), as determined by hand-lens or petrographic analysis. Corresponds to a rock typically containing 15 percent iron by weight.</skos:definition>
      <skos:narrower rdf:resource="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/codelist/LithologyValue/ironRichSedimentaryRock"/>
