      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">non-clastic siliceous sedimentary material</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Sedimentary material that consists of at least 50 percent silicate mineral material, deposited directly by chemical or biological processes at the depositional surface, or in particles formed by chemical or biological processes within the basin of deposition.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Sedimentary material that consists of at least 50 percent silicate mineral material, deposited directly by chemical or biological processes at the depositional surface, or in particles formed by chemical or biological processes within the basin of deposition.</skos:definition>
