      <dct:title xml:lang="en">phosphorite</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">phosphorite</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Sedimentary rock in which at least 50 percent of the primary or recrystallized constituents are phosphate minerals. Most commonly occurs as a bedded primary or reworked secondary marine rock, composed of microcrystalline carbonate fluorapatite in the form of lamina, pellets, oolites and nodules, and skeletal, shell and bone fragments.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Sedimentary rock in which at least 50 percent of the primary or recrystallized constituents are phosphate minerals. Most commonly occurs as a bedded primary or reworked secondary marine rock, composed of microcrystalline carbonate fluorapatite in the form of lamina, pellets, oolites and nodules, and skeletal, shell and bone fragments.</skos:definition>
      <skos:broader rdf:resource="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/codelist/LithologyValue/phosphateRichSedimentaryMaterial"/>
