      <dct:title xml:lang="en">granite</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">granite</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Phaneritic crystalline rock consisting of quartz, alkali feldspar and plagioclase (typically sodic) in variable amounts, usually with biotite and/or hornblende. Includes rocks defined modally in QAPF Field 3.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Phaneritic crystalline rock consisting of quartz, alkali feldspar and plagioclase (typically sodic) in variable amounts, usually with biotite and/or hornblende. Includes rocks defined modally in QAPF Field 3.</skos:definition>
