      <dct:title xml:lang="en">gabbroic rock</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">gabbroic rock</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Gabbroid that has a plagioclase to total feldspar ratio greater than 0.9 in the QAPF fraction. Includes QAPF fields 10*, 10, and 10'. This category includes the various categories defined in LeMaitre et al. (2002) based on the mafic mineralogy, but apparently not subdivided based on the quartz/feldspathoid content.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Gabbroid that has a plagioclase to total feldspar ratio greater than 0.9 in the QAPF fraction. Includes QAPF fields 10*, 10, and 10'. This category includes the various categories defined in LeMaitre et al. (2002) based on the mafic mineralogy, but apparently not subdivided based on the quartz/feldspathoid content.</skos:definition>
      <skos:narrower rdf:resource="http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/codelist/LithologyValue/quartzGabbro"/>
