      <dct:title xml:lang="en">dioritic rock</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">dioritic rock</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Phaneritic crystalline rock with M less than 90, consisting of intermediate plagioclase, commonly with hornblende and often with biotite or augite. A dioritoid with a plagioclase to total feldspar ratio (in the QAPF fraction) greater than 0.9. Includes rocks defined modally in QAPF fields 10, 10' and 10*.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Phaneritic crystalline rock with M less than 90, consisting of intermediate plagioclase, commonly with hornblende and often with biotite or augite. A dioritoid with a plagioclase to total feldspar ratio (in the QAPF fraction) greater than 0.9. Includes rocks defined modally in QAPF fields 10, 10' and 10*.</skos:definition>
