      <dct:title xml:lang="en">diorite</dct:title>
      <skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">diorite</skos:prefLabel>
      <dct:description xml:lang="en">Phaneritic crystalline rock consisting of intermediate plagioclase, commonly with hornblende and often with biotite or augite; colour index M less than 90, sodic plagioclase (An0-An50), no feldspathoid, and between 0 and 5 percent quartz. Includes rocks defined modally in QAPF field 10 as diorite.</dct:description>
      <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Phaneritic crystalline rock consisting of intermediate plagioclase, commonly with hornblende and often with biotite or augite; colour index M less than 90, sodic plagioclase (An0-An50), no feldspathoid, and between 0 and 5 percent quartz. Includes rocks defined modally in QAPF field 10 as diorite.</skos:definition>
